'''Théo Bernard François Hernandez''' ({{IPA|fr|teo ɛʁnɑ̃dɛz, - ɛʁnandɛs}};<ref>{{cite web |date=27 March 2022 |title=Le OUI-NON avec les FRÈRES Hernandez ! |trans-title=The YES-NO with the Hernandez BROTHERS ! |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ms8PQ5ou-Xo&t=95s |access-date=2 July 2023 |website=YouTube |language=fr}}</ref> born 6 October 1997) is a French professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays primarily as a [[left-back]] for [[Saudi Pro League]] club [[Al Hilal SFC|Al Hilal]] and the  [[France national football team|France national team]]. He is known for his speed, dribbling, and goal scoring ability.<ref>
*{{cite web |title=Best defenders in the world 2023 |url=https://www.radiotimes.com/tv/sport/football/best-defenders-world/ |access-date=8 August 2023 |website=Radio Times}}
*{{cite web |date=20 May 2023 |title=Top 10 Best Full-backs In The World 2023 |url=https://www.footballorbit.com/best-full-backs-world-2023/ |access-date=8 August 2023 |website=FootballOrbit |archive-date=10 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230810230114/https://www.footballorbit.com/best-full-backs-world-2023/ |url-status=dead }}
*{{cite web |last=Soriano |first=Joe |date=1 July 2023 |title=Ranking the 10 best left backs in the world right now in 2023 |url=https://thetrivelaeffect.com/best-left-backs/ |access-date=8 August 2023 |website=The Trivela Effect}}
*{{cite web |last=Khan |first=Kamran |date=27 May 2023 |title=Top 10 Best Left Backs In The World 2023 |url=https://www.sportshubnet.com/top-10-best-left-backs-in-the-world/ |access-date=8 August 2023 |website=Sportshubnet}}
*{{cite web |last=Mukherjee |first=Swarup |date=13 June 2023 |title=Top 10 Best Left Backs In Football 2023 |url=https://sillyseason.com/list/top-10/best-left-backs-in-football-79470/ |access-date=8 August 2023}}</ref>

Théo is the younger brother of fellow professional footballer [[Lucas Hernandez]],<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-04-28 |title=13 fun facts about Theo Hernandez {{!}} Goal.com English Qatar |url=https://www.goal.com/en-qa/lists/13-fun-facts-about-theo-hernandez/blta54fdad649ed2b1b#cs0aa1dd1c69c576d5 |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-QA}}</ref> and the son of [[Jean-François Hernandez]], a retired footballer.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Théo Hernandez |url=https://theflashsports.com/player/theo-hernandez/ |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=Flash Sports Entertainment |language=en-US}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Atlético Madrid===
Born in [[Marseille]], Hernandez moved to Spain at the age of two. He then joined [[Atlético Madrid]]'s [[Atlético Madrid (youth)|academy]] in 2007, aged nine.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/20140917/atletico-madrid/lucas-y-theo-hernandez-sociedad-defensora-ilimitada_54415127039.html |title=Lucas y Theo Hernández, sociedad defensora ilimitada|trans-title=Lucas and Theo Hernández, defensive company unlimited |newspaper=[[Mundo Deportivo]] |first=Chema |last=G. Fuente |language=es |date=17 September 2014|access-date=21 July 2016}}</ref> After progressing through the youth categories, he was promoted to [[Atlético Madrid B|the reserves]] in [[Tercera División]] in summer 2015.{{citation needed|date=November 2022}}

On 3 February 2016, Hernandez renewed his contract.<ref>{{cite news |date=3 February 2016 |title=Theo ficha por el primer equipo |language=es |trans-title=Theo signs for the first team |newspaper=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]] |url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/atletico/2016/02/03/56b1caf5ca474113488b4642.html |access-date=21 July 2016}}</ref> Two days later, he was called up to the first team for a [[La Liga]] match against [[SD Eibar|Eibar]] due to injuries,<ref>{{cite news |last=Díaz |first=Francisco Javier |date=5 February 2016 |title=Simeone forced into rookie back line for Eibar visit |newspaper=[[Diario AS]] |url=http://en.as.com/en/2016/02/05/football/1454685303_897218.html |access-date=21 July 2016 |archive-date=15 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210515042142/https://en.as.com/en/2016/02/05/football/1454685303_897218.html |url-status=dead }}</ref> but remained an unused [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] in the 3–1 home win.<ref>{{cite news |last=Malagón |first=Manuel |date=6 February 2016 |title=Fiesta completa en el Calderón |language=es |trans-title=Complete party at the Calderón |newspaper=Marca |url=http://www.marca.com/eventos/marcador/futbol/2015_16/la-liga/jornada_23/atm_eib/ |access-date=21 July 2016}}</ref>

===Alavés===
On 4 August 2016, Hernandez extended his contract until 2021, being immediately loaned to fellow league club [[Deportivo Alavés|Alavés]] for one year.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2016-08-04 |title=Club Atlético de Madrid - Theo Hernández renews until 2021 |url=https://en.atleticodemadrid.com/noticias/theo-hernandez-renews-until-2021 |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=Club Atlético de Madrid |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.deportivoalaves.com/noticia/theo-hernandez-juventud-y-desparpajo-en-el-lateral-albiazul |title=Theo Hernández, juventud y desparpajo en el lateral albiazul|trans-title=Theo Hernández, youth and pizzazz for the blue-and-white flank |publisher=Deportivo Alavés |language=es |date=4 August 2016|access-date=5 August 2016}}</ref> He made his professional debut late in the month, starting in a 0–0 home draw with [[Sporting de Gijón]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.marca.com/eventos/marcador/futbol/2016_17/la-liga/jornada_2/ala_spo/ |title=Alavés y Sporting siguen sumando buenas sensaciones|trans-title=Alavés and Sporting pile up the good feelings |newspaper=Marca |first=Jordi |last=Castelló |language=es |date=28 August 2016|access-date=28 August 2016}}</ref>

On 16 October 2016, Hernandez was given a straight [[Ejection (sports)|red card]]<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |date=2025-01-30 |title=Athletic produce stirring comeback to win Basque derby |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/sports/soccer/athletic-produce-stirring-comeback-to-win-basque-derby-idUSL4N1CM0DC/ |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=Reuters |language=en-GB}}</ref> in a 1–1 home draw to [[Málaga CF|Málaga]] after a hard [[Tackle (football move)|tackle]] on [[Ignacio Camacho]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.noticiasdealava.com/2016/10/17/alaves/la-roja-a-theo-la-primera-expulsion-en-lo-que-va-de-curso?random=937239 |title=La roja a Theo, la primera expulsión en lo que va de curso |trans-title=Theo red card, the first ejection of the campaign |publisher=Noticias de Álava |language=es |date=17 October 2016 |access-date=5 July 2017 |archive-date=28 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170828105836/http://www.noticiasdealava.com/2016/10/17/alaves/la-roja-a-theo-la-primera-expulsion-en-lo-que-va-de-curso?random=937239 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=":0" /> He scored his first professional goal the following 7 May, netting the game's only goal in a home victory over [[Athletic Bilbao]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2017-06-05 |title=Alavés vs Athletic: Theo lía la Eurozona |trans-title=Theo befuddles the Eurozone |url=https://www.marca.com/eventos/marcador/futbol/2016_17/la-liga/jornada_36/ala_ath/ |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=MARCA.com}}</ref> A regular starter during the [[Basque Country (autonomous community)|Basque]] team's [[2016–17 Copa del Rey|run]] in the [[Copa del Rey]], Hernandez helped them reach [[2017 Copa del Rey Final|the final]] for the first time in their 91-year history. During the decisive match on 27 May 2017, he scored the equaliser through a [[direct free kick]] in an eventual 1–3 loss against [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Barcelona 3-1 Alavés (May 27, 2017) Final Score |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match?gameId=474318 |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref>

===Real Madrid===
[[File:Theo Hernández.jpg|thumb|Hernandez celebrating after winning the [[2017–18 UEFA Champions League]] with [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]]|left|210x210px]]
On 5 July 2017, Hernandez signed a six-year deal with [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] after they met his release clause of €24 million.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2017-07-05 |title=Madrid sign Theo from rivals Atletico |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/story/_/id/37526061/real-madrid-sign-theo-hernandez-atletico-madrid-six-year-deal |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2017-07-05 |title=Club Atlético de Madrid - Theo Hernández, traspasado al Real Madrid |trans-title=Theo Hernández, transferred to Real Madrid |url=https://www.atleticodemadrid.com/noticias/theo-hernandez-traspasado-al-real-madrid |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=Club Atlético de Madrid |language=es-ES}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=2017-07-05 |title=Real Madrid sign Theo Hernandez from Atletico Madrid, as Fabio Coentrao leaves |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/40510914 |access-date=2025-04-05 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> He made his competitive debut on 16 August, replacing [[Marco Asensio]] in a 2–0 home win against Barcelona for [[2017 Supercopa de España|that year]]'s [[Supercopa de España]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Bull |first=J. J. |date=2017-08-16 |title=Real Madrid 2 Barcelona 0 (5-1 on aggregate): Woeful Barca dismissed as Zinedine Zidane's unstoppable side win Super Cup |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2017/08/16/real-madrid-vs-barcelona-spanish-super-cup-live-score-updates/ |access-date=2025-04-05 |work=The Telegraph |language=en-GB |issn=0307-1235}}</ref>

Hernandez made three appearances during the [[2017–18 UEFA Champions League|2017–18 edition]] of the [[UEFA Champions League]],<ref>{{Cite web |last=Radio |first=R. C. N. |date=2018-05-25 |title=Champions: Así llegan Real Madrid y Liverpool |trans-title=That is how Real Madrid and Liverpool arrive to the Champions final |url=https://www.rcnradio.com/deportes/asi-llegan-las-plantillas-de-real-madrid-y-liverpool-la-final-de-la-champions |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=RCN Radio |language=spanish}}</ref> helping the club win its third consecutive and 13th overall title in the competition.<ref>{{Cite web |last=UEFA.com |title=Madrid beat Liverpool to complete hat-trick |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0245-0e98d7318379-716954065574-1000--madrid-beat-liverpool-to-complete-hat-trick/ |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=UEFA.com |language=en}}</ref> On 10 August 2018, he was loaned to [[Real Sociedad]].<ref>{{Cite web |date= |title=Agreement for Theo Hernández to play on loan |url=https://www.realsociedad.eus/en/news/details/agreement-for-theo-hernandez-to-play-on-loan |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=www.realsociedad.eus |language=en}}</ref>

===AC Milan===
On 7 July 2019, Hernandez joined [[Serie A]] club [[A.C. Milan|AC Milan]] in a deal worth maximum of €20 million.<ref>{{Cite web |last=G. Medina |first=David |date=2019-06-28 |title=Theo Hernandez set to join AC Milan on six-year deal |url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/real-madrid/2019/06/28/5d16166222601dad138b45b8.html |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=MARCA in English |language=en}}</ref> The transfer was approved and carried out by [[Paolo Maldini]], who met with him informally in [[Ibiza]] to persuade him to join.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-04-04 |title=Theo Hernandez reveals how Maldini was decisive in sealing Milan move |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/theo-hernandez-reveals-how-maldini-was-decisive-in-sealing-milan-move-28231319?variable=20200126 |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=OneFootball |language=en}}</ref> Hernandez made his debut on 21 September, playing 18 minutes in the 2–0 defeat against [[Inter Milan]] in the [[Derby della Madonnina]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sport.sky.it/calcio/serie-a/2019/09/21/milan-inter-risultato-gol |title=Milan-Inter 0–2: gol e highlights della partita. Brozovic-Lukaku, nerazzurri primi|trans-title=Milan-Inter 0–2: match goals and highlights. Brozovic-Lukaku, black-and-blue first |publisher=[[Sky Sport (Italy)|Sky Sport]] |language=it |date=21 September 2019|access-date=31 January 2020}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the ''Rossoneri'' on 5 October, helping the visitors come from behind to win 2–1 at [[Genoa C.F.C.|Genoa]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.repubblica.it/sport/calcio/serie-a/2019/10/05/news/genoa-milan_1-2_paqueta_e_leao_trasformano_il_diavolo-237792182/ |title=Genoa-Milan 1–2, Hernandez e Kessié rilanciano Giampaolo|trans-title=Genoa-Milan 1–2, Hernandez and Kessié relaunch Giampaolo |newspaper=[[La Repubblica]] |first=Marco |last=Gaetani |language=it |date=5 October 2019|access-date=31 January 2020}}</ref> During his first season with Milan he managed to score 7 goals in all competitions and had 3 [[Assist (association football)|assists]].<ref name=":1">{{Cite web |last=AS |first=Diario |date=2025-03-31 |title=Theo Hernández: player stats, career and honors of the Milan |url=https://en.as.com/resultados/ficha/deportista/theo_hernandez/34782/ |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=AS.com |language=en-us}}</ref>
[[File:TheoHernandez2022Salzburg.jpg|thumb|226x226px|Hernandez with [[A.C. Milan|AC Milan]] in 2022]]
On 23 December 2020, Hernandez's 93rd-minute winning goal gave AC Milan a victory over [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]] to keep them top of Serie A.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2020-12-23 |title=AC Milan 3-2 Lazio: Theo Hernandez's late winner keeps Milan top of Serie A |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/55428707 |access-date=2025-04-05 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> During the 2020–21 season, Hernandez was the only defender in the top five European leagues to have scored two braces. He was also the defender with the most successful dribbles in Serie A that season with 73.<ref>{{Cite web |title=AC Milan, all the numbers from Serie A 2020/2021 |url=https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/articles/stats/2021-05-30/ac-milan-all-the-numbers-from-serie-a-2020-21 |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=AC Milan |language=en}}</ref> During his second season with the team, he managed to score 8 goals and assisted 7 in all competitions.<ref name=":1" />

On 6 January 2022, Hernandez wore the captain's armband for the first time against [[A.S. Roma|Roma]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-02-11 |title=Theo Hernandez: "There were many teams that wanted me, but I only thought about Milan" |url=https://sempremilan.com/theo-hernandez-many-teams-milan |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=SempreMilan |language=en}}</ref> Three days later, he scored a brace in a 3–0 win against [[Venezia F.C.|Venezia]], becoming first defender to score at least three braces in AC Milan's Serie A history.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Venezia ... AC Milan, Serie A TIM 2021/2022: stats |url=https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/articles/stats/2022-01-09/venezia-v-ac-milan-the-numbers-from-the-game |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=AC Milan |language=en}}</ref> On 11 February, Hernandez renewed his contract with Milan until 2026.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Theo Hernández renews his contract with AC Milan: the official statement |url=https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/articles/media/2022-02-11/official-statement-theo-hernandez |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=AC Milan |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Heyes |first=Apollo |date=2022-02-11 |title=Official: Theo Hernandez extends his contract with Milan to 2026 - Football Italia |url=https://football-italia.net/official-theo-hernandez-extends-his-contract-with-milan-to-2026/ |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=football-italia.net |language=en-GB}}</ref> On 15 May 2022 against Atalanta, Hernandez ran for 95 metres before scoring the second goal of a 2–0 win.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Fisher |first=Oliver |date=2022-05-15 |title=AC Milan 2-0 Atalanta: Rossoneri on the brink of the Scudetto as Leao and Theo score |url=https://sempremilan.com/milan-2-0-atalanta-match-report/amp |access-date=2025-04-05 |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Campanale |first=Susy |date=2022-05-15 |title=Theo Hernandez: 'I thought, I'm going all the way' - Football Italia |url=https://football-italia.net/theo-hernandez-i-thought-im-going-all-the-way/ |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=football-italia.net |language=en-GB}}</ref> A week later, Milan were crowned with their first Serie A title in 11 years, Hernandez's contributions were 5 goals and 6 assists, the most for any defender in Serie A that season.<ref>{{Cite web |title=AC Milan, Serie A TIM 2021/22: stats |url=https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/articles/stats/2022-05-24/19-scudetto-facts |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=AC Milan |language=en}}</ref>

On 25 October 2023, Hernandez faced his older brother, [[Lucas Hernandez|Lucas]], for the first time as an opponent playing competitive senior football in the [[UEFA Champions League]] group stage away game against [[Paris Saint-Germain]], a 3–0 loss for Milan.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.uefa.com/news-media/mediaservices/informationkits/competitions/uefachampionsleague/2024/match/2039125/ | title=UEFA PressKits }}</ref> The two faced each other once again two weeks later, with Milan prevailing 2–1 at home and Théo assisting the winning goal scored by [[Olivier Giroud]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=UEFA.com |title=History: Milan 2-1 Paris: UEFA Champions League 2023/24 Group stage |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2039134--milan-vs-paris/ |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=UEFA.com |language=en}}</ref> On 2 December 2023, amidst an injury crisis in Milan's central defense, Hernandez volunteered to play as a centre-back for the first time in his senior career and was highly praised for his performance by the Italian football media as Milan won 3–1 against [[Frosinone Calcio|Frosinone]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Le pagelle di Theo: tutti abbiamo uno sconosciuto dentro di noi, il suo fa il centrale |url=https://www.milannews.it/news/le-pagelle-di-theo-tutti-abbiamo-uno-sconosciuto-dentro-di-noi-il-suo-fa-il-centrale-516625 |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=Milan News |language=it}}</ref>

On 27 September 2024, Hernandez contributed to a 3–0 win against [[U.S. Lecce|Lecce]] with a goal, which became his 29th in the Serie A.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-09-28 |title=AC Milan 3-0 Lecce: Five things we learned - Theao and defensive worries |url=https://sempremilan.com/ac-milan-3-0-lecce-five-things-learned-2024 |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=SempreMilan |language=en}}</ref> As a result, he equaled Paolo Maldini's goalscoaring record for AC Milan in the Serie A competitions and was praised on social media by the club and Maldini himself.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Bai |first=Alessandro |date=2024-09-28 |title=Theo Hernandez sends message to Maldini after equalling his Milan record in Serie A |url=https://football-italia.net/theo-hernandez-maldini-message-record-milan/ |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=football-italia.net |language=en-GB}}</ref>

On 6 October 2024, his 27th birthday, Hernandez had a controversial game in [[Florence]], which ended in a 2–1 loss for Milan to [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]], followed by his post-game argument with a referee that culminated in a [[Penalty card#Red card|red card]] and a subsequent two-game suspension. During the first half, Hernandez caused a penalty (shot saved by [[Mike Maignan]]) and failed to score from the penalty spot himself, with his shot saved by [[David de Gea]]. In the second, he assisted the equalizing goal scored by [[Christian Pulisic]] with a curling cross from the left side and nearly caused another penalty kick for a risky tackle inside Milan's penalty box, with the referee ultimately deciding against it after a video review.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-04-04 |title=GdS: Penalty conceded, penalty missed, red card – Theo Hernandez's disastrous birthday |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/gds-penalty-conceded-penalty-missed-red-card-theo-hernandezs-disastrous-birthday-40138853 |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=OneFootball |language=en}}</ref> On 14 January 2025, he scored his 30th Serie A goal for Milan in a 2–1 away victory over [[Como 1907|Como]], becoming the club's highest-scoring defender, surpassing [[Paolo Maldini]]'s previous record.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Theo Hernández Surpasses Paolo Maldini as AC Milan's Top-Scoring Defender |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/serie-a/articles-video/theo-hern%C3%A1ndez-surpasses-paolo-maldini-as-ac-milan-s-top-scoring-defender-2025-01-14 |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=beIN SPORTS |language=en-us}}</ref>

===Al Hilal===
On 10 July 2025, Hernandez joined [[Saudi Pro League]] club [[Al Hilal SFC|Al Hilal]] permanently, for an estimated €25 million fee.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.alhilal.com/ar/news/thyw-hyrnadyz-hlaly-ana-lthlathh-aawam|title=
"ثيو هيرناديز" هلاليـًا لثلاثة أعوام}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/articles/media/2025-07-10/official-statement-theo-hernandez|title=OFFICIAL STATEMENT: THEO HERNÁNDEZ}}</ref>

In early January 2026, Italian reports suggested Juventus were in talks over a move to bring Hernandez back to Serie A from Al Hilal, including claims of a verbal agreement and that he “misses Italy”.<ref>{{Cite web |last=read |first=Football Italia·2 min |date=2026-01-04 |title=Report Juventus in talks over deal for ex-Milan star Theo Hernandez |url=https://ca.sports.yahoo.com/news/report-juventus-talks-over-deal-150000841.html |access-date=2026-01-08 |website=Yahoo Sports |language=en-US}}</ref>

==International career==
On 26 April 2018, Hernandez received his first call to the [[France national football team|France]] senior squad.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fff.fr/article/3280-la-liste-des-vingt-trois-bleus.html |title=La liste des vingt-trois Bleus |website=fff.fr |date=26 August 2021 |accessdate=26 August 2021}}</ref> He made his debut on 7 September 2021 in a [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group D|World Cup qualifier]] against [[Finland national football team|Finland]], a 2–0 home victory. He started and played the whole game.<ref>{{cite web |publisher=[[FIFA]] |url=https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/mens/worldcup/qatar2022/qualifiers/uefa/match-center/400155627 |title=France v Finland game report |date=7 September 2021}}</ref> In October 2021, ahead of the [[2021 UEFA Nations League Finals|UEFA Nations League]] semi-finals against [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]], Théo for the first time received a call-up to the national team from [[Didier Deschamps]] together with his brother [[Lucas Hernandez|Lucas]]; the two were later fielded in the 3–4–1–2 formation as a left centre-back and a left wing-back, respectively, making it the first time they played together in a senior competitive game.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://as.com/futbol/2021/10/05/internacional/1633439250_629806.html |title=El sueño de los Hernández |date=5 October 2021}}</ref> On 7 October, he scored a late-time winner in the 3–2 victory against the aforementioned opponent, sending his team to the [[2021 UEFA Nations League Final|final]] for the first time in history of the tournament.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/58837332 |title=Belgium 2 France 3 |date=7 October 2021 |work=BBC Sport |accessdate=8 October 2021}}</ref>

In November 2022, Hernandez was named in France's final squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] in Qatar.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Bleus-une-liste-de-25-pour-la-coupe-du-monde-avec-giroud-mandanda-et-saliba/1364022|title=Bleus : une liste de 25 pour la Coupe du monde avec Giroud, Mandanda et Saliba|trans-title=A 25-player list for the World Cup with Giroud, Mandanda and Saliba|newspaper=[[L'Équipe]]|language=fr|date=9 November 2022|access-date=9 November 2022}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Sportstar |first=Team |date=2022-11-09 |title=France squad for FIFA World Cup 2022: Deschamps announces 25-man provisional team, Benzema to lead attack |url=https://sportstar.thehindu.com/football/fifa-world-cup/news/fifa-world-cup-france-squad-full-team-player-list-injury-list-international-football/article66117006.ece |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=Sportstar |language=en}}</ref> On 14 December, he scored a goal in a 2–0 win over [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]] in the semi-finals.<ref>{{cite web |author=Nick Wright |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/12766794/world-cup-2022-france-2-0-morocco-theo-hernandez-and-randal-kolo-muani-on-target-as-didier-deschamps-side-reach-final |title=World Cup 2022 - France 2-0 Morocco: Theo Hernandez and Randal Kolo Muani on target as Didier Deschamps' side reach final |website=Sky Sports |date=15 December 2022 }}</ref>

In June 2024, he was named in the squad for [[UEFA Euro 2024]] in Germany.<ref>{{cite news |date=16 May 2024 |title=Les vingt-cinq Bleus pour l'Euro |trans-title=The twenty-five Blues for the Euro |url=https://www.fff.fr/article/12507-les-vingt-cinq-bleus-pour-l-euro.html |language=fr |publisher=[[French Football Federation]] |access-date=16 May 2024}}</ref> In their quarter-final match against [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] on 5 July, he scored the winning penalty kick of the [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|shoot-out]] to send his country into the next round.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/news/028f-1b4c52293b81-d35abf4d3953-1000--portugal-0-0-france-aet-3-5-pens-les-bleus-edge-through-on-/ |title=Portugal 0–0 France (aet, 3–5 pens): Les Bleus edge through on spot-kicks |website=[[UEFA]] |publisher=Union of European Football Associations |date=19 November 2023}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Hernandez's father, [[Jean-François Hernandez|Jean-François]], was also a footballer. A [[centre-back]] from France, he too played for [[Atlético Madrid]];<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.ladepeche.fr/article/2018/03/21/2764068-lucas-hernandez-l-espagnol-a-l-accent-francais.html |title=Lucas Hernandez, l'Espagnol à l'accent français|trans-title=Lucas Hernandez, the Spaniard with the French accent |newspaper=[[La Dépêche du Midi]] |first=Sébastien |last=Barrère |language=fr |date=21 March 2018|access-date=1 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.abc.es/atletico-madrid/noticias/20141205/abci-lucas-hernandez-atletico-201412051718.html |title=Lucas, el futuro jefe de la defensa|trans-title=Lucas, the future boss of the defence |newspaper=[[ABC (newspaper)|ABC]] |language=es |date=5 December 2014|access-date=21 July 2016}}</ref> his older brother [[Lucas Hernandez|Lucas]], who plays for [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] and [[France national football team|France]], was also developed at the club.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/atletico-madrid/20160206/301951417690/atletico-atletico-de-madrid-atleti-lucas-hernandez-theo-hernandez.html |title=Theo y Lucas, dos hermanos del Atlético sobre el campo 60 años después|trans-title=Theo and Lucas, two brothers from Atlético on the field 60 years later |newspaper=Mundo Deportivo |first=Chema |last=G. Fuente |language=es |date=6 February 2016|access-date=21 July 2016}}</ref> In 2022, French newspaper ''[[L'Équipe]]'' found that Jean-François – who went missing in 2004 – was living in Thailand, and had allegedly been legally blocked by his ex-partner from seeing their children.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-11-12 |title=Father of Lucas and Theo Hernandez 'turns up' 18 years later: He's waiting for his children to call him |url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/2022/11/12/636f792ce2704e9c7f8b4590.html |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=MARCA |language=en}}</ref>

He has been dating Italian model Zoe Cristofoli since June 2020.<ref>{{cite web |title=Theo Hernandez Girlfriend - Zoe Cristofoli |url=https://ohmyfootball.com/news/812/hernandez-wife-zoe-cristofoli|access-date=11 October 2021 |website=ohmyfootball.com |date=6 August 2021 }}</ref> On 8 April 2022, the couple's son was born.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Zoe Cristofoli e Theo Hernandez sono diventati genitori: le prime foto del figlio |url=https://www.today.it/gossip/vip/zoe-cristofoli-theo-hernandez-figlio-foto.html |access-date=2023-01-30 |website=Today |language=it}}</ref>

